<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-10T10:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-10T10:48:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–1054: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/><gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss></hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-10T11:48:00-04:00">May 10, 1954—11:48
                                        a.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 114. Department’s <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 111 sent Seoul 904 and Tokyo
                                    2468;<note n="1" xml:id="d139fn1">Dated May 9, <ref target="#pg_237">p. 237</ref>.</note> Seoul’s 1139<note n="2" xml:id="d139fn2">Dated May 9, <ref target="#pg_237"><hi rend="italic">ibid</hi></ref>.</note> and 1140<note n="3" xml:id="d139fn3"><ref target="#d138"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi></ref>.</note> repeated Geneva 64 and 65
                                Tokyo 673 and 675. Department has reconsidered and does not desire
                                discussion Plan B with working group in Geneva mentioned in
                                paragraph 1 reference Department telegram.</p>
                            <pb facs="0268" n="242" xml:id="pg_242"/>
                            <p>Increasing seriousness Indochina situation underlines undesirability
                                open break with <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> over
                                presentation Plan B which we like him recognize has serious
                                practical difficulties if Communists were to accept. Efforts
                                persuade him agree to presentation Plan B should continue along
                                lines already indicated. Especially desirable have <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> recommend it from Geneva if
                                not already done.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>